Sept 18 (Reuters) - The following are the top stories in the Financial Times. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

Headlines   CAPITAL SHORTFALLS LIKELY TO EMERGE FROM UNPRECEDENTED ECB PROBE(http://on.ft.com/1rbUZ6i)BUG IN APPLE HEALTHKIT HITS IOS 8 LAUNCH (http://on.ft.com/1uacXo9)   BANKS' VAT BILLS SET TO SOAR AFTER EUROPE COURT RULING (http://on.ft.com/1mcAhCT)  U.S. WARNS OF FURTHER INSIDER TRADING CHARGES (http://on.ft.com/1sqOAQV)WELLS FARGO EASES LENDING REQUIREMENTS FOR APARTMENT PURCHASES (http://on.ft.com/1ASCkgx)  Overview  A European Central Bank led probe of the euro area banking sector has been billed as a once-and-for-all opportunity to kill the impending crisis of confidence that is hindering lending in the region.   A bug in HealthKit, Apple Inc's <AAPL.O> new health and fitness tracking software app, threatened to overshadow the launch of the company's new iOS 8 iPhone operating system on Wednesday. Many app developers found that their apps had been removed from Apple's App Store due to the unspecified bug.   Banks and insurers in Europe are bracing for extra value added tax bills that could run into billions of euros after an unexpected ruling by the European Court of Justice over a dispute between Skandia America Corporation and the Swedish tax authority.